{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Add \u201cJewish\u201d to the list of ethnic group categories for all government forms",
        "additional_details": "Antisemitism has in recent history been a racial, not just religious, prejudice. Hitler's Nazis did not spare non-believing or converted Jews.\r\n \r\nLike many people born into Jewish families, I claim \"Jewish\" as a definition of my ethnic identity (DNA testing identifies me as Ashkenazi Jewish). I have no religious beliefs. I believe listing \"Jewish\" as only a religion reflects and fosters ignorance about Jewish ethnicity, and the roots of antisemitism.",
        "background": "Add \u201cJewish\u201d as a mandatory ethnicity option for all government forms that collect data on ethnicity, include the official census. According to current practice (including the census form) \"Jewish\" is listed only as a religion, which could exclude, say, ethnically Jewish atheists.",
